The Smart Parking System was tested to check its ability to detect available and occupied parking slots.
During operation, the ultrasonic sensors continuously measured the distance in each parking slot. When a vehicle was placed in front of the sensor, the system detected a reduced distance and marked the slot as occupied. When the vehicle was removed, the slot was updated as free.
The Arduino processed the sensor data accurately and displayed the parking status on the LCD in real time. The system responded quickly to changes and updated the display without delay.
The project worked reliably under different conditions and showed consistent performance. It helped in identifying parking availability easily without manual checking.
Overall, the system demonstrated efficient parking management, real time monitoring, and reduced effort in finding available parking spaces.

